[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]A grab-bag of menu and HUD tweaks. Every option is independently toggleable, so pick the parts you want and ignore the rest.[/size]

[size=3][b]Save &amp; loading[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Quick Save[/b] — saves your progress (not your position) on a configurable keybind. Useful before something risky.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Continue button[/b] — adds a Continue option to the main menu that loads your most recently played save.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Auto-load on startup[/b] — optionally loads your most recent save the moment the game finishes booting. Hold Left Shift during loading to skip and stay on the menu.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Menu cleanup[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Hide the noise[/b] — toggle off the social-media buttons, DLC ads, patch notes, and developer logo on the main menu, individually.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]DLC carousel handling[/b] — DLC you already own is greyed out instead of being pitched at you. The DLC shop button can be hidden entirely.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Quit to Desktop[/b] — adds a proper quit-to-desktop button on the in-game settings panel, so you don't have to bounce through the main menu.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Skip "missing items" dialogue[/b] — interacting with a museum display no longer prompts the missing-items popup every time.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Emotes &amp; fast dialogue[/b] — toggle the emote wheel and the fast-dialogue option independently of each other.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Gameplay tweaks[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Adjustable quest tracker[/b] — the quest tracker on the right of the screen can be made taller so it fits more lines.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Move-speed multiplier[/b] — flat multiplier applied before any vanilla speed buffs. Two keybinds for in-game increase/decrease.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]"Has Materials" selected by default[/b] — opening any crafting table has the materials filter pre-selected.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Health &amp; mana regen[/b] — optional, off by default. Slow trickle so it doesn't trivialise combat.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Start away from the mailbox[/b] — when loading, the player is placed a configurable distance from the mailbox instead of right on top of it.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Audio &amp; display[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Mute when unfocused[/b] — game audio mutes when the window isn't focused. Resumes the moment you click back in.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Force resolution update on scene change[/b] — fixes display issues some users hit when the game's resolution doesn't apply correctly after a scene transition.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/7]UI Scales[/url] — independent scale for almost every UI surface. Pairs naturally with the menu-cleanup tweaks here.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/199]Auto Tools[/url] — automatically swaps to the right tool based on what you're aiming at, so the move-speed buff actually saves you time.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/27]No Time For Fishing[/url] — skip the fishing minigame entirely.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/222]No Time To Stop &amp; Eat[/url] — eat without stopping.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/31]Keep Alive[/url] — required by this mod; keeps everything loaded between play sessions.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/30]Sun Haven BepInEx Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/30][size=3]Sun Haven BepInEx Pack[/size][/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/31][size=3]Keep Alive[/size][/url]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Compatibility[/b][/size]

[size=3]Built and tested against the latest Steam build of Sun Haven.[/size]

[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...\steamapps\common\Sun Haven\BepInEx\plugins[/code][/size]

